        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "For much of its history, the ACA‚Äôs premium tax credits only went to poorer families, creating what was known as a "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            7
          ],
          1,
          "‚Äúsubsidy cliff‚Äù"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " that made it difficult for middle-class households to afford exchange plans. The American Rescue Plan expanded the eligibility criteria for these subsidies, with the policy "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            8
          ],
          1,
          "halving"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " monthly premium payments for millions of Americans."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Those subsidies are set to expire soon; without their extension, millions of marketplace enrollees would receive notices about sharp premium increases in October, shortly before the November midterm elections. Making matters worse: Insurers are preparing to hike premiums more than they have in recent years, with a median proposed increase of 10 percent for Americans on individual plans, according to a recent "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            4
          ],
          1,
          "review"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " by the Peterson Center on Healthcare and the Kaiser Family Foundation."
